abstract: From lava lights to vinyl wallpaper to role that lights in the dark, a look at what’s making news now.
snippet: From lava lights to vinyl wallpaper to role that lights in the dark, a look at what’s making news now.
lead_paragraph: When a news release announced that kitchen rugs were the latest home design trend, some were skeptical. After all, it’s hard enough keeping kitchen floors clean without an add-on that harbors pet hair and cooking splatters.

headline_main: Lady Gaga Isn’t Done Shape-Shifting Yet

abstract: The president has long sold himself as a self-made billionaire, but a Times investigation found that he received at least $413 million in today’s dollars from his father’s real estate empire, much of it through tax dodges in the 1990s.

abstract: The Opéra National de Paris begins a big birthday season with “Les Huguenots” and “Bérénice,” two takes on past glories of French culture.

abstract: With Republicans holding a one-vote edge in the Senate, Democrats are focused on unseating Martin Golden, the last Republican senator in Brooklyn.
snippet: With Republicans holding a one-vote edge in the Senate, Democrats are focused on unseating Martin Golden, the last Republican senator in Brooklyn.
lead_paragraph: Deep in the heart of Brooklyn, a borough virtually synonymous with deep blue politics, lies an unlikely battleground for control of the New York State Senate.
